docs.abstract: Friction over how Attorney General William P. Barr handled the Mueller report underscored a gap between the ideal and political reality of his post.
docs.snippet: Friction over how Attorney General William P. Barr handled the Mueller report underscored a gap between the ideal and political reality of his post.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Attorney General William P. Barr said during his confirmation hearing in January that serving in his future post was “not the same” as representing President Trump and pledged to make law enforcement decisions based only on facts and the law — not politics.

headline.print_headline: Team Player for President And the Top Legal Referee
